[SN]TITLE[SN]
Giorgio 'Giuseppe' Roncari death: Tribute to 'twin with big heart'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The death of an Italian man whose body was found at a house in Greater Manchester has "left an unbearable emptiness", his family have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Giorgio Roncari, who was also known as Giuseppe, was discovered in Blackburn Street, Salford, on 17 April.
Police said a post-mortem examination had failed to establish the cause of his death.
The 61-year-old's family said he had been a "loving uncle" and "a twin brother with a big heart".
Det Insp Andy Butterworth said a murder investigation was continuing and officers were "actively searching for those responsible for his death".
